Thanks for sharing your itinerary ! How did you arrange transport? Love the next to last, the antepenultimate and the fourth from last photos. Iâ€™ve commissioned a painting of each of them I highly recommend climbing â€â™‚ï¸ Mount Jirisan even though youâ€™re not in the southern region of the South Korea  since the extra cost of traveling there is offset by cheap entrance fee. Climbing it is an arduous journey but the view is worth it. In fact my friend who went there last month showed me his photos by which I was awestruck. At night, even though two of the nearby lakes have dried up, the remaining lakes reflect the beauty of the stars  and Mount Jirisan giving a double view of the starry sky and the mountains â›° The shake of Mount Jirisan is clearly defined against the starry nights  by which youâ€™ll be awestruck. He said it was well worth it for the view from the mountaintop and the confidence that heâ€™d gained afterwards. Again, the low admission charge offsets the rising transportation fees so itâ€™s worth a visit! Last week my Korean friend Jae-Ho asked whether I wanted to join him for supper at his home. I replied in the affirmative. We washed two boxes of salad  and left the salad to dry out before consuming it. In this way the salad contains more nutrients than eating it right after you open the lid. After supper, I said "Iâ€™ll wash  you dry" He came to the kitchen and stood beside me drying up the cutlery and utensils while I washed. Since itâ€™s best to dry your clothes out the night before by hanging them on the clothesline, I went ahead and did that. Then I joined his sister on a run along the promenade. I bought a pair of trainers  for her who said she would pay me back if I got her those sneakers. Looks like she sold me a pup. In addition I bought a Chanel belt but Iâ€™m wondering if this really is authentic. I might have been sold a bill of goods.â€â™‚ï¸ I gave her a foot massage afterwards and dried her feet on a towel and a quilt. Jae-Ho is a human resource manager. I admire his ambition and ruthless determination to succeed. Heâ€™s so focused on his work that he never gets sidetracked by personal issues. Recently, his brother has broken up with his girlfriend so heâ€™s feeling a little bit down. To those couples who have broken up and havenâ€™t yet found new love: Take heart ! You might find it worth your while to read "Men are from Mars women are from Venus" written by John Gray. Heâ€™s a relationship expert whose work elaborates the keys  to successful long term relationship. I was reluctant to read it at first since Iâ€™m not an avid reader but it turned out to be worth my while as Iâ€™ve learnt loads about how men and women think differently. Many successful couples say this international bestseller is worth its weight in gold to them. You can also consult a social worker for what itâ€™s worth.
